<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-009-039 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 522 086</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Nov 21 1991 n1809* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple's A/UX 3.0 roadmap points to the Quadra. (ProductAnnouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   A/UX 3.0 (Operating system) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUNIXUNIX-Like Operating SystemsReduced-instruction-set computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>APPLE's A/UX 3.0 ROADMAP POINTS TO THE QUADRAandM;Apple Computer has unveiled details of its newest release of Unix, A/UX 3.0.andO;More than just an operating system upgrade, A/UX 3.0 is a &quot;roadmap&quot; for itsfuture Unix directions and thefoundation for high-end computers it willrelease in the future, Apple told Microbytes.andP;  These will include systemsbased on the PowerPC RISC processor that Apple and Motorola are developingwith IBM, which will run the PowerOpen Unix operating system.andP;  The newversion of A/UX will be compatible with System 7.0, including such featuresas the new Finder, TrueType fonts, the Data Access Manager, and Balloon Help.andO;It will also support interapplication communication, using thepublish/subscribe mechanism that lets one application automatically receiveupdated information from another application.andP;  A/UX 3.0 will be a full SystemV.2 version of Unix providing multitasking, multiuser, and virtual memoryfeatures.andP;  Although users will be able to take advantage of these featureswith a completely Mac-like GUI, Unix junkies will still have access to thecommand line interface, through a special window that they can open whileperforming other graphical operations.andP;  The ability to run current Macapplications is perceived as crucial to the new A/UX's success - programsrunning on the new version of A/UX will look just like regular Macapplications.andP;  By announcing A/UX 3.0 now, Apple is trying to give customersanother reason to buy Quadra-class machines, since these best use thesoftware.andO;</TEXT></DOC>